<chapter id="configuration.folder">
  <title id="configuration.folder.title">Configuration folder</title>
  <para>The configuration folder contains most of the user preferences.</para>
  <note><para>If anything happens to your OmegaT installation and you can't seem
  to fix it, the first step is to stop OmegaT, create a backup of the
  configuration folder's contents, delete the original configuration folder it
  and restart OmegaT.</para></note>

  <section id="configuration.folder.location">
    <title id="configuration.folder.location.title">Configuration folder location</title>
	<para>The configuration folder is where most of the OmegaT parameters are
	stored for a given user.</para>
	<para>The configuration folder's location depends on your computer (the
	<emphasis>~</emphasis> character corresponds to the user's home directory):
	<variablelist>
	  <varlistentry><term>Linux</term><listitem><para><filename>~/.omegat</filename></para></listitem></varlistentry>
	  <varlistentry><term>macOS</term><listitem><para><filename>~/Library/Preferences/OmegaT</filename></para></listitem></varlistentry>
	  <varlistentry><term>Windows</term><listitem><para><filename>~\AppData\Roaming\OmegaT</filename></para></listitem></varlistentry>
	</variablelist>
	</para>
	<para>You can always access the configuration folder directly with <link
	linkend="menus.options.access.configuration.folder"
	endterm="menus.options.access.configuration.folder.title"/> from the <link
	linkend="menus.options" endterm="menus.options.title"/> menu.</para>
  </section>
  
  <section id="configuration.folder.default.contents">
    <title id="configuration.folder.default.contents.title">Configuration folder
    default contents</title>
	<variablelist>
	  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.omegat.prefs">
		<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.omegat.prefs.title">omegat.prefs</term>
		<listitem><para>This file includes a number of important user
		preferences.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
	  
	  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.uilayout">
		<term
		id="configuration.folder.default.contents.uilayout.title">uiLayout.xml</term>
		<listitem><para>This file describes the OmegaT's general layout.</para>
	</listitem>
	  </varlistentry>
	  
	  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.logs">
		<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.logs.title">logs/</term>
		<listitem><para>This folder contains a number of log files, of which the
		most current is <filename>OmegaT.log</filename>.</para>
		<para>This file records Java messages while OmegaT is running. Should
		OmegaT appear to be behaving erratically, it is important to include
		this file or the relevant part in any bug report.</para>
		<para>That file is also available from <link linkend="menus.help.log"
		endterm="menus.help.log.title"/> in the <link linkend="menus.help"
		endterm="menus.help.title"/> menu.</para>
		</listitem>
	  </varlistentry>

	  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script">
		<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.title">script/</term>
		<listitem><para>This folder can contain 3 text files:
		<variablelist>
		  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.selection">
			<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.selection.title">selection.txt</term>
			<listitem><para>This file contains the selection when <link
			linkend="menus.edit.export.selection"
			endterm="menus.edit.export.selection.title"/> in the <link
			linkend="menus.edit" endterm="menus.edit.title"/> is used. The file
			contents is updated every time the function is
			called.</para></listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  
		  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.source">
			<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.source.title">source.txt</term>
			<listitem><para>This
		file contains the <emphasis>source</emphasis> part of the current
		segment when <link
		linkend="dialogs.preferences.editor.export.the.segment.to.text.files"
		endterm="dialogs.preferences.editor.export.the.segment.to.text.files.title"/>
		in the <link linkend="dialogs.preferences"
		endterm="dialogs.preferences.title"/> menu is set. The file contents is
		updated every time a new segment is
			entered.</para></listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
		  <varlistentry id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.target">
			<term id="configuration.folder.default.contents.script.target.title">target.txt</term>
			<listitem><para>This file contains the <emphasis>target</emphasis>
			part of the current segment when <link
			linkend="dialogs.preferences.editor.export.the.segment.to.text.files"
			endterm="dialogs.preferences.editor.export.the.segment.to.text.files.title"/>
			in the <link linkend="dialogs.preferences"
			endterm="dialogs.preferences.title"/> is set. The file contents is
			updated every time a new segment is
			entered.</para>
			</listitem>
		  </varlistentry>
	  </variablelist>
	  
	  The three files can be used as a simple way to access some contents from
	  OmegaT and to process it with local programs (shell scripts, etc.).
	  </para></listitem></varlistentry>
	</variablelist>
  </section>
  
    <section id="configuration.folder.extra.contents">
    <title id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.title">Configuration folder
    extra contents</title>

	<variablelist>
	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.editorshortcuts">
	  <term
	  id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.editorshortcuts.title">EditorShortcuts.properties</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized editor shortcuts parameters
	  file. See <link linkend="appendix.shortcut.customization"
	  endterm="appendix.shortcut.customization.title"/> for
	  details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.maninmenushortcut">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.maninmenushortcut.title">MainMenuShortcuts.properties</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized user interface shortcuts
	  parameters file. See <link linkend="appendix.shortcut.customization"
	  endterm="appendix.shortcut.customization.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.filters">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.filters.title">filters.xml</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized file filters parameters
	  file. See <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.file.filters"
	  endterm="dialogs.preferences.file.filters.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.finder">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.finder.title">finder.xml</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized external search parameters
	  file. See <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.external.searches"
	  endterm="dialogs.preferences.external.searches.title"/> for
	  details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.omegat.autotext">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.omegat.autotext.title">omegat.autotext</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized autotext parameters file. See
	  <link linkend="dialog.preferences.auto.completion"
	  endterm="dialog.preferences.auto.completion.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.repositories">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.repositories.title">repositories.properties</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your team projects repositories login
	  information file. <warning><para>Contents are not
	  encrypted.</para></warning>See <link linkend="how.to.setup.team.project"
	  endterm="how.to.setup.team.project.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.segmentation">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.segmentation.title">segmentation.conf</term>
	  <listitem><para>This file is your customized segmentation parameters
	  file. See <link linkend="dialogs.preferences.segmentation.setup"
	  endterm="dialogs.preferences.segmentation.setup.title"/> for
	  details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	
	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.plugin">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.plugin.title">plugins/</term>
	  <listitem><para>This folder is an alternative location for OmegaT
	  extension plugins that you manually install. See <link
	  linkend="dialogs.preferences.plugins"
	  endterm="dialogs.preferences.plugins.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>

	<varlistentry id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.spelling">
	  <term id="configuration.folder.extra.contents.spelling.title">spelling/</term>
	  <listitem><para>This folder contains your spelling dictionaries. See <link
	  linkend="spellchecker.installing.dictionaries"
	  endterm="spellchecker.installing.dictionaries.title"/> for details.</para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
	</section>
	
  <section id="configuration.folder.setting">
	<title id="configuration.folder.setting.title">Configuration folder setting</title>
	<para>You can specify a configuration folder different from the default one
	when you start OmegaT from the command line.</para>
	<para>When you do that, all the
	preferences set from the <link linkend="dialogs.preferences"
	endterm="dialogs.preferences.title"/> dialog will be registered in that
	folder and won't be available to other instances of OmegaT that will start
	with a different configuration folder. See <link linkend="launch.with.command.line.omegat.parameters" endterm="launch.with.command.line.omegat.parameters.title"/> for details.</para>
  </section>
</chapter>
